race.description: St Johns Park Bowling Club Handicap (Bm64)
race.comment: SPIRIT OF WEALTH (2) resumed in a high rating contest when taking control early before fading in the straight to finish sixth over 1100m at Randwick in BM78 class behind Monte Supreme and Chidiac. That form has since been franked, and the two trials should have her back on track. Goes close. LADY MEMPHIS (10) will be at her peak for this, and the fast tempo gives her a great winning chance. Closed quickly when producing fast closing splits when a narrow second over 1000m at Muswellbrook. Drops in weight from the good draw. TANGO QUEEN (9) win record hardly excites but expected to have strengthened over the break. Can roll forward from the low gate with the two trials under her belt. STILL ALICE (3) held ground to the line over this track and trip when a fighting second on September 25. Kept fresh and due for a change of luck.
